**Summary:** HEAVY day — oil crashing 5%+ on Iran ceasefire hopes, gold surging to $4,575 ATH, broad risk-on with Russell leading (+1.34%). Space sector is the standout (5 watchlist names >3%), nuclear uranium names rallying while CEG diverges (-2.9%), and critical minerals bouncing on reduced Iran copper supply threat. Key headlines: ARM's 136-core chip (+12%), Pentagon $13B Maven AI commitment for PLTR, SK Hynix $8B ASML order, NASA lunar base pivot, and 500 GWh US storage forecast. NRC Part 53 final rule drops Friday. Still in the post-Triple Witch bearish window with AAPL blackout starting tomorrow — cautiously bullish bias with structural headwinds.
